cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes an improvement to the existing data-driven Neural Belief Tracking (NBT) framework for Dialogue State Tracking (DST). 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a statistical update mechanism for modelling dialogue dynamics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed update mechanism involves learning jointly with the semantic decoding and context modelling parts of the NBT model. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with dialogue state tracking which involves processing spoken language. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for dialogue state tracking.
